   <refnamediv>
       <refname>maokts </refname>
               <refpurpose>k-periods uncentered moving average for a time series </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>xma = maokts(xts,k)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> xts </term> =    a time series</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> k </term> =    size of the moving average</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> xma </term> =    the filtered serie (with the same size of xts)</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Computes k-periods uncentered moving average. The first (k-1)-values of the moving average are compute by "pading" the first initial values of the time serie.
 
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
 
x=reshape(grand(200,1,'nor',0,1),'1945q1');
xma = maokts(x,12)
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Emmanuel Michaux (2007)
        </refsection>
</refentry>
